beastiary:ability_posing_riddles a beast:Ability ;
    rdfs:label "Posing Riddles"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The intellectual capacity to challenge others through cryptic questions or complex linguistic puzzles; it functions as a test of wisdom or a mechanism for defense, requiring the interlocutor to provide a specific solution to avoid misfortune."@en,
        "The riddle performs an intellectual diairesis, forcing the separation of truth from falsehood and embodying the diaretic drive toward analysis and absolute distinction."@en ;
    beast:belongsToImaginaryStructure beast:SchizomorphicStructure ;
    beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol beast:DiareticSymbol ;
    beast:isGovernedBy beast:DiurnalRegime .

beastiary:ability_speed a beast:Ability ;
    rdfs:label "Speed"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Durand's scheme ties the teriomorphic directly to 'restlessness caused by rapid, undisciplined movement' and 'fleeing from devouring time,' making animal speed a near-definitional fit."@en,
        "Exceptional swiftness of movement on land, in water, or in the air."@en ;
    beast:belongsToImaginaryStructure beast:SchizomorphicStructure ;
    beast:embodiesImaginarySymbol beast:TeriomorphicSymbol ;
    beast:isGovernedBy beast:DiurnalRegime .

